  <a name='usage'></a>
  <section='usage'>
  <h3>Using DoMosaics</h3>
  <div style='text-align: justify;'>
  <hr />
  <p style='text-align:justify;'>As mentioned below, DoMosaics is work in progress. We have not yet finished with the application, 
  and we have also not yet completed a manual. In a nutshell, on *nix systems, do</p>
  <pre>[12:59] radmoore@joshua ~/Desktop $ java -jar domosaics.jar</pre>
  <p style='text-align:justify;'>to start DoMosaics. On windows, a double click will presumably do the job. Most users will want to start with a set of fasta sequences, 
  run the annotator (against <%= link_to "InterPro", "http://www.ebi.ac.uk/interpro/" %>) to annotate domains, and then associate the resulting domain architectures 
  to leafs of a tree. A crude tree can be calculated using DoMosaics, but we recommend using proper software for that 
  (eg. <%= link_to "RaxML", "http://icwww.epfl.ch/~stamatak/index-Dateien/Page443.htm" %> or <%= link_to 'FastTree', "http://www.microbesonline.org/fasttree/" %> ).
  You will probably get the hang of things by messing with the menus and wizards. We shall update this page with a manual once were ready.</p>
  </div>
