  <a name='faq'></a>
  <section id='faq'>
  <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
  <hr />
  <ul>

    <li>
    <em>Wait a minute... this site used to host a program called DoMosaics</em>
    <p style='text-align:justify'>No worries - DoMosaics is identical to AnGSTD. AnGSTD was more of a working title, and as we are approaching
    the first real release, we reconsidered naming options. There is no need to be concerned about webcites pointing to angstd.uni-muenster.de -
    they will be redirected to domosaics.uni-muenster.de</p>
    </li>

    <li>
    <em>I am using DoMosaics under Windows...</em>
    <p style='text-align:justify;'>Most things should work under windows, but there are still a couple of issues. We have not yet ensured tested
    the Windows port of HMMER, but that is planned for the nearest future. We hope to have full windows support in the next release. For now
    if you are having problems under windows, <a href="#contact">contact</a> us with some details and will get back to you.</p>
    </li>

    <li>
    <em>When I start DoMosaics I get "The default workspace is currently in use ...</em>
    <p style='text-align:justify;'>This can happen when DoMosaics crashes violently, and can not clean up after itself. Navigate to the workspace folder you created
    when you started DoMosaics the first time (default is USER_HOME/.angstd-workspace) and remove the .lock file.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <em>How do I get started? Is there a manual?</em>
    <p style='text-align:justify;'>Unfortunately, we do not yet have a manual. In the current release, we added two example data sets for users to use a bit prior
    'production' use. We suggest starting with one of these data sets (which can be found under Help). In general, it is probably easiest to
    start with a set of protein sequences (fasta format), and load them into DoMosaics (File -> New -> Project with data -> create a project -> select fasta file)
    Once the view is loaded, run a search for domains using InterProScan (Annotate -> InterPro) to create a domain view.</p>
    </li>
    
    <li>
    <em>I am getting a java error: </em>
    <pre>Exception in thread "main" java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space</pre>
    <p style='text-align:justify;'>This indicates that the <%= link_to 'Java virtual machine', "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_virtual_machine" %>
    has run out of memory. Try increasing the amount of memory allocated to the VM. To do so, on *unix systems, do</p>
    <pre>
    [13:04] radmoore@joshua ~/Desktop $ java -Xms512m -Xmx1024m -jar domosaics.jar</pre>
    <p>to increase the initial and the max. size of your VMs heap space. Windows users must
    <%= link_to 'google', "http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&q=windows+increase+heap+size+JVM&aq=f&aqi=&aql=&oq=&gs_rfai="%></p>
    </li>

    <li>
    <em>Apparently, my question is not frequently asked...</em>
    <p>Understandable. Don't hesitate, <a href="contact">contact</a> us. We love the feedback...</p>
    </li>

  </ul>
